This paper deals with statistical learning with local differential privacy, which involves information theory (IT) and machine learning (LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing local private mechanisms, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (CR). The optimization problem studied in the paper involves discrete distribution estimation, which is a topic in data structures (DS) and algorithms. Finally, the proposed mechanism involves probability assignments, which is a topic in computational complexity (CC).
